Comment 12: 
Here are details of your problem:

 <ProblemSignatures>
  <EventType>BEX64</EventType> 
  <Parameter0>a.out.exe</Parameter0> 
  <Parameter1>0.0.0.0</Parameter1> 
  <Parameter2>4fbe82a9</Parameter2> 
  <Parameter3>a.out.exe</Parameter3> 
  <Parameter4>0.0.0.0</Parameter4> 
  <Parameter5>4fbe82a9</Parameter5> 
  <Parameter6>0000000000043b90</Parameter6> 
  <Parameter7>c0000005</Parameter7> 
  <Parameter8>0000000000000008</Parameter8> 
  </ProblemSignatures>
  - 

The important bit is c0000005 - it means you are reading or writing memory that you are
not allowed to access. I am not certain, but, I think, 4fbe82a9 is your PC. Perhaps,
this will help you find offending line.

It would be nicer if your program would print stack trace instead. But, as I pointed out
earlier  https://golang.org/issue/3543, sometimes it does not
happens.

Alex
